    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka stocks plunge over 2-pct in mid-day trade on fuel crisis",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s stock market fell over 2 percent on June 27 after a four-session gain on the fear of an economic standstill due to lack of fuel in the country, Colombo Stock Exchange data showed.",
        "The main All Share Price Index slipped 2.06 percent or 157.74 points to 7,490.45 at 1130 hours.",
        "\u201cThe market crashed in the first hour on the fear that the country will come to a standstill this week as the country runs out of fuel and has no confirmation when the next fuel consignment will arrive in the country,\u201d a top market analyst told Economy Next.",
        "THe most liquid index down 2.44 percent or 60.37 points to 2,409.82.",
        "The top losers in the first hour were Expolanka, Browns Investment and LOLC Holdings. (Colombo/June27/2022)"
      ],
